  "text": "Dynamic contrast-enhanced (DCE)-MRI is an advanced imaging technique that has recently demonstrated promise for distinguishing between different primary brain tumor histologies [CITATION_1] . Unlike conventional imaging, DCE-MRI can quantitatively assess tumor microvasculature by measurement of a range of parameters that reflect specific physiologic characteristics such as plasma volume (Vp) and volume transfer coefficient (K trans ).",
